at, compare `02h` and `03h` more directly on price-state behavior to decide which one is the better shadow candidate for future overnight experimentation.\n\n---\n## 2026-04-23 03:46 UTC \u2014 [P2: Smart Entry] Turn Overnight Non-Execution Hours Into a Real Research Asset by Measuring Their Bias Structure Instead of Treating Them as Dead Time\n\n**Task:** Use the overnight non-execution window for actual strategy research by measuring the bias structure inside `OUTSIDE_ACTIVE_HOURS` logs, rather than continuing to treat those hours as operationally blank.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive.\n- In the recent overnight blocked sample:\n  - observations: `331`\n  - mean bias: `13.29`\n  - median bias: `31.1`\n  - min bias: `-85.9`\n  - max bias: `81.5`\n  - strong-bias windows (`|bias| >= 45`): `150`\n  - strong-bias share: `45.3%`\n  - negative windows: `115`\n  - positive windows: `216`\n- That means overnight hours are non-execution, but **not** low-information.\n- Wrote research artifact: `/home/ubuntu/clawd/patches/v10n-overnight-bias-structure-research.spec.md`\n\n**My thi",
